The paper deals with the analysis of the rate-reliability-complexity limits of the quasi-static K-user multiple access channel (MAC), with or without feedback. This involves the study of information theory, networking, and system engineering, which are all covered by the arXiv categories of cs.IT, cs.NI, and cs.SY. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning (ML) for decoding, which falls under the category of cs.MM (machine learning). Finally, the paper explores the interdependencies between complexity, feedback, and performance, which is a topic that can be relevant to the category of cs.LG (machine learning).
